```python
def largest_difference(numbers):
    if len(numbers) < 2:
        return None
    else:
        return max(numbers) - min(numbers)
```

This function first checks if the list has less than 2 elements. If so, it returns None because you can't have a difference between one number. Otherwise, it returns the maximum number in the list minus the minimum number in the list.
